node.text:
The Morning.
.
.
My new risograph comic “Morning” is now available, link in my bio!
.
Beautifully printed by @risolve , “Morning” is a 36 page 9.75” x 7.5” comic.  Printed in blue, bubblegum, and sunflower, this comic really pops in the light. 
.
Thank you to everyone who has bought a copy, I am really excited to share this book with you all. I spent a long time on this book and I think its one of the more personal stories I’ve ever told. So I hope you all enjoy “Morning” and i am looking forward to making more work like this.
.
.
Orders start going out this week!
.

Photo by Evan M. Cohen on June 18, 2021. May be an illustration.

node.text:
I am very excited to release my new comic “Morning”, along with a new shirt and print design, all now available at the link in my bio.
.
.
Beautifully printed by @risolve, “Morning” is a 36 page comic, 9.75” x 7.5”, printed in 3 vibrant eye popping colors. 
.
“Morning” is a story about moving on and accepting that our lives will change. We never know when something will be the last time we get to experience it.  How do you live in the moment if you are preparing to say goodbye? Life has no set path, things change for better or worse. The sun keeps rising every morning either way.
.
“Crystallized” shirts printed by @beezerprinting 
.
I also restocked the rest of the prints from the last release too, head to the link in my bio to see what’s available! Thanks everyone!
.
.
.

Photo by Evan M. Cohen on June 04, 2021. May be a cartoon.

node.text:
Summer love.
.
.
From my comic “Eternal” printed last year.  This sequence really holds a place in my heart. I felt like this comic was pouring out of me when I was working on it. I think it ended up as one of my strongest books, trying to dive back into this feeling again. Hope it helps you as much as it helped me.
.
.
.
.
